TEXT 56 -208 Left 2 ;Notes:\n1) The capacitor stops all the constant voltage and therefore removes the constant DC offset (if there is any)\n \nDesign:\n1) Cut-off frequency is 1/(2*pi*R*C) = 1.592kHz.\nAt cut off there is attenuation of -3 dB (by definition). That is Vout = Vin/sqrt(2)
